🔥 What is Rate Limiting?
✅ Interview Answer

Rate limiting is a technique used to control the number of requests a user/client can make to an API within a specific time period.

🧠 Simple Explanation

“Rate limiting prevents users from sending too many requests in a short time, protecting the system from overload or abuse.”

🏢 Real-Time Example
💼 Scenario: Login API
Max 5 requests per minute per user
If user exceeds:
→ API returns HTTP 429 (Too Many Requests)
User → Login API (5 times allowed)
6th request → BLOCKED ❌
