🔥 What is Config Server?

👉 Config Server = Centralized configuration management system

Instead of storing configs in every microservice,
👉 we keep them in one central place and all services fetch from there.

🔹 Why do we need it?
❌ Without Config Server:

Each service has its own config:

Order Service → application.properties
Payment Service → application.properties
User Service → application.properties

👉 Problem:
Duplicate configs (DB URL, API keys)
Hard to update
Need redeploy for every change
✅ With Config Server:
             [ Config Server ]
                    |
        --------------------------
        |           |            |
   Order Service  Payment   User Service

👉 All services fetch configs from one place

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Where configs are stored?

👉 Usually in Git Repository

Example:

config-repo/
   order-service.yml
   payment-service.yml
   application.yml   (common configs)
🔹 Architecture Diagram
        [ Git Repo ]
             |
             v
      [ Config Server ]
             |
   -----------------------
   |         |           |
[Order]   [Payment]   [User]
 Service    Service    Service
🔹 How it works (Step-by-step)
1. Config Server starts
Connected to Git repo
2. Microservice starts (e.g., Order Service)

👉 It calls Config Server:

GET /order-service/default
3. Config Server responds

Returns:

DB URL
Username
Password
Other configs
4. Service uses these configs at runtime
🔹 Spring Boot Code (Basic)
✅ Config Server
@EnableConfigServer
@SpringBootApplication
public class ConfigServerApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(ConfigServerApplication.class, args);
    }
}
