🔥 13. What is Saga Pattern?
✅ Answer
Manages distributed transactions.

🧠 Scenario
Order placed:

Order created
Payment failed → rollback order

Two types:
Choreography
Orchestration

🔹 1. Choreography (Event-Based)

👉 No central controller
👉 Services communicate via events (Kafka/RabbitMQ)

Flow:
Order Created → Event
       ↓
Payment Service listens → tries payment
       ↓
Payment Failed → Event
       ↓
Order Service listens → cancels order
========================================
🔹 2. Orchestration (Central Controller)

👉 One service controls everything (Orchestrator)

Flow:
Orchestrator → Order Service (create)
Orchestrator → Payment Service (pay)
If fail:
Orchestrator → Order Service (cancel)
